The design was the work of Mr. H.H. Wilkinson who was the Distributor of Stamps in Pretoria. The design consisted of a full-face portrait of King George V., surmounted by a crown, the name of the country appears above and below the King's head in the English and Afrikaans languages, while the four corners contains shields on which the heraldic insignia of the Colonies comprising the Union are shown. 

